included.headline: University of Michigan Presidential Postdoctoral Fellow

included.description: I volunteer at a Senior Center in the Chicagoland area (anonymous to protect the identity of individuals) where I hold "office hours" to help seniors with any technology problem they have. Over the years, the most asked questions are regarding unopened iPads that residents' children and grandchildren buy as gifts. Other notable sessions have led to residents creating tasks on TaskRabbit, asking "What is the cloud?", and helping residents print out news articles for their friends who can't make it to the computer lab.

I am a Code Coach for Brave Initiatives - https://www.braveinitiatives.com/ which motivates high school girls in Chicago to pursue computing through a more holistic approach of focusing on solving problems in their communities, understanding components of good design, finding their voice, communicating their ideas, and coding.
